      system      : "Linux"
      type        : FILE_CHECK
      description : "9.1.2 Set User/Group Owner and Permission on /etc/crontab"
      info        : "The /etc/crontab file is used by cron to control its own jobs. The commands in this item
make sure that root is the user and group owner of the file and that only the owner can
access the file.

